doc.after: The territory is the approximate shape of a right triangle bordering the U S state of Alaska to the west for 1 210 km 752 miles mostly along longitude 141 W the Northwest Territories to the east and British Columbia to the south Its northern coast is on the Beaufort Sea Its ragged eastern boundary mostly follows the divide between the Yukon Basin and the Mackenzie River drainage basin to the east in the Mackenzie mountains Its capital is Whitehorse
